===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=the bird|-}}

# The vulgar hand gesture in which the middle finger is extended.
#* '''2003''', ''The Beach House'', James Patterson&mdash;Then she raised both hands above her shoulders and flipped him the bird with each one.

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[brid]]'', “young bird”, “chick”, of unknown origin.

See also ''[[burd]]''.

====Noun====
[[Image:Blue Tit aka.jpg|thumb|right|A small bird, definition 1]]
{{en-noun}}

# A member of the [[class]] of [[animal]]s ''[[Aves]]'' in the [[phylum]] [[Chordata]], characterized by being warm-blooded, having [[feather]]s, [[wing]]s usually capable of [[flight]], and laying [[egg]]s.
#: ''Ducks and sparrows are '''birds'''.''
# (''UK, slang'') A person.
#: ''He’s an odd '''bird'''.''
# (''UK, slang'') A girl or woman considered sexually [[attractive]], as used by a man.
#: ''Who’s that '''bird'''?''
# {{context|Irish|slang}} Girlfriend.
#: ''Anto went out with his '''bird''' last night.''

